OL,3,CThe oil shock looks over, but we'll be
OL,4,Ccounting the cost of this war for a
OL,5,Cwhile
OL,7,FBefore the war, up to 140 ships passed
OL,8,Fin and out of the Persian Gulf each
OL,9,Fday - many of them carrying gas, oil
OL,10,Fand refined products like diesel and
OL,11,Fjet fuel.
OL,13,FIn the first week of June, the average
OL,14,Fwas just seven a day.
OL,16,FAccording to analysis from the marine
OL,17,Fintelligence firm Windward, 35 vessels
OL,18,Fhave been damaged since the conflict
OL,19,Fbegan - most of them in Iranian
OL,20,Fattacks - but at least three ships
OL,21,Fhave also been "disabled" by US forces.
