OL,3,CThe oil shock looks over, but we'll be
OL,4,Ccounting the cost of this war for a
OL,5,Cwhile
OL,7,FBut it's striking that oil peaked at
OL,8,F$118 a barrel at the end of March -
OL,9,Faround $20 below the peak reached
OL,10,Fafter Russia invaded Ukraine in 2022 -
OL,11,Fdespite a warning from the
OL,12,FInternational Energy Agency that the
OL,13,Fshock could be worse than those of
OL,14,F2022, 1973 and 1979 combined.
OL,16,FThe war has caused widespread damage
OL,17,Fto oil and gas infrastructure across
OL,18,Fthe Gulf, including ports, refineries,
OL,19,Fprocessing plants, pipelines and
OL,20,Fstorage depots.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/7
